1
00:00:22,689 --> 00:00:27,160
(woman)
Once upon Christmas
in the 21st century--

2
00:00:27,193 --> 00:00:28,028
(man)
No, no, no.

3
00:00:28,061 --> 00:00:30,864
Once there was
this French guy--me--

4
00:00:30,897 --> 00:00:32,565
here in Mexico,

5
00:00:32,599 --> 00:00:35,568
and he wanted to be
a bullfighter.

6
00:00:35,602 --> 00:00:37,704
(woman)
Uh, well, let's--okay.

7
00:00:37,737 --> 00:00:38,805
This French bullfighter

8
00:00:38,838 --> 00:00:40,440
didn't know much
about Christmas.

9
00:00:40,473 --> 00:00:41,841
(man)
It's not a Christmas story.

10
00:00:41,875 --> 00:00:43,309
That's a very important part.

11
00:00:43,343 --> 00:00:44,711
It's much,
much more complicated.

12
00:00:44,744 --> 00:00:47,447
It's about a man--
French guy--me--

13
00:00:47,480 --> 00:00:49,716
(woman)
Okay, well, obviously,
you know the story.

14
00:00:49,749 --> 00:00:50,717
You tell the story.

15
00:00:50,750 --> 00:00:51,785
(man)
No, no, do it,

16
00:00:51,818 --> 00:00:53,353
but I think
we are totally agree.

17
00:00:53,386 --> 00:00:55,422
(woman)
Okay, the story
revolves around you,

18
00:00:55,455 --> 00:00:56,856
so sure.

19
00:01:05,198 --> 00:01:06,166
[woman clears throat]

20
00:01:06,199 --> 00:01:10,336
Once there was a battle
between good and evil.

21
00:01:10,370 --> 00:01:11,438
(man)
Yes, that's right.

22
00:01:11,471 --> 00:01:13,239
It was terrible,
and this French guy--

23
00:01:13,273 --> 00:01:15,442
oh, yeah, it's more about--

24
00:01:15,475 --> 00:01:17,744
(woman)
Oh, okay, we're not gonna--
tell the story.

25
00:01:17,777 --> 00:01:19,279
(man)
No, no, I think it's not--

26
00:01:19,312 --> 00:01:20,280
(woman)
Yes.

27
00:01:20,313 --> 00:01:21,414
(man)
Yes, yes, but, no,

28
00:01:21,448 --> 00:01:23,183
it's much more complicated
than that.

29
00:01:23,216 --> 00:01:24,784
(woman)
Okay, okay,
just watch this.

30
00:01:24,818 --> 00:01:25,819
(man)
Okay, watch this.

31
00:01:25,852 --> 00:01:29,422
[electronic whirring sounds]

32
00:01:29,456 --> 00:01:35,228
(woman #2)
♪ Are you going

33
00:01:35,261 --> 00:01:40,900
♪ to Scarborough Faire?

34
00:01:40,934 --> 00:01:44,938
♪ Parsley, sage,

35
00:01:44,971 --> 00:01:52,946
♪ rosemary, and thyme.

36
00:01:52,979 --> 00:01:57,250
♪ Remember me

37
00:01:57,283 --> 00:02:03,590
♪ to one who lives there.

38
00:02:03,623 --> 00:02:09,229
♪ Once he was

39
00:02:09,262 --> 00:02:13,566
♪ a true love of mine.  ♪

40
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:14,834
Hey!

41
00:02:14,868 --> 00:02:18,771
[lights thunking]

42
00:02:18,805 --> 00:02:19,739
Ah.

43
00:02:22,008 --> 00:02:23,943
(girl)
Big French Jacques.

44
00:02:23,977 --> 00:02:26,446
I just wanna see how big.

45
00:02:26,479 --> 00:02:30,283
[screeching noises]

46
00:02:30,316 --> 00:02:35,421
You want a real bull?

47
00:02:35,455 --> 00:02:38,258
[snorting]

48
00:02:39,759 --> 00:02:40,727
[giggles]

49
00:02:40,760 --> 00:02:41,561
Like you always say,

50
00:02:41,594 --> 00:02:43,563
if you love me,
show me.

51
00:02:43,596 --> 00:02:47,667
[rock music]

52
00:02:47,700 --> 00:02:52,605
(man)
♪ I feel you.

53
00:02:52,639 --> 00:02:55,842
♪ Your sun, it shines.

54
00:02:55,875 --> 00:02:58,978
♪

55
00:02:59,012 --> 00:03:04,417
♪ I feel you

56
00:03:04,450 --> 00:03:10,023
♪ within my mind.

57
00:03:10,056 --> 00:03:12,025
♪ You take me there.

58
00:03:12,058 --> 00:03:13,526
I'm not dead yet,
pretty bull.

59
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:15,995
(man)
♪ The kingdom comes.

60
00:03:16,029 --> 00:03:21,401
♪ You take me to Babylon.

61
00:03:21,434 --> 00:03:22,802
Diablo!

62
00:03:22,835 --> 00:03:24,671
(man)
♪ This is the morning
of our love. ♪

63
00:03:24,704 --> 00:03:27,807
No!

64
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:29,475
[girl grunts]

65
00:03:29,509 --> 00:03:31,244
(man)
♪ This is the morning
of our-- ♪

66
00:03:38,751 --> 00:03:40,053
What happened?

67
00:03:40,086 --> 00:03:41,588
(man)
It's okay.
It's okay.

68
00:03:41,621 --> 00:03:42,789
[bull grunting]

69
00:03:56,469 --> 00:03:57,737
I'll get help.

70
00:03:57,770 --> 00:04:00,673
Daddy won't understand.

71
00:04:00,707 --> 00:04:02,575
Go now.

72
00:04:02,609 --> 00:04:05,478
(man)
Hey, who turned on
the goddamn lights?

73
00:04:05,511 --> 00:04:06,746
I'll tell what happened.

74
00:04:06,779 --> 00:04:11,484
Yeah, go now.

75
00:04:11,517 --> 00:04:14,454
[metal clanking]

76
00:04:14,487 --> 00:04:15,755
(man)
Who let the damn bull out?

77
00:04:15,788 --> 00:04:18,758
[indistinct voices]

78
00:04:21,394 --> 00:04:24,364
(man)
Oh, God damn it!

79
00:04:33,740 --> 00:04:36,509
Mr. Cordobes!

80
00:04:36,542 --> 00:04:39,679
Mr. Cordobes!

81
00:04:39,712 --> 00:04:40,680
Mr. Cordobes!

82
00:04:40,713 --> 00:04:42,749
Good boy.

83
00:04:42,782 --> 00:04:43,850
Mr. Cordobes!

84
00:04:43,883 --> 00:04:45,718
Your daughter!

85
00:04:45,752 --> 00:04:47,887
[breathing heavily]

86
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:51,891
It's Laila.

87
00:04:51,924 --> 00:04:53,393
(Cordobes)
How'd this happen?

88
00:04:53,426 --> 00:04:54,861
Jacques.

89
00:04:54,894 --> 00:04:56,062
Get the boys,
and find him.

90
00:04:56,095 --> 00:04:56,896
All right.

91
00:04:56,929 --> 00:04:58,965
(Cordobes)
Call a doctor.

92
00:04:58,998 --> 00:05:01,000
[door creaking]

93
00:05:01,034 --> 00:05:02,135
[gun cocks]

94
00:05:02,168 --> 00:05:04,103
[gunshots]

95
00:05:04,137 --> 00:05:05,071
[distant gunshot]

96
00:05:17,650 --> 00:05:19,752
Jones.

97
00:05:19,786 --> 00:05:21,487
Yeah.

98
00:05:21,521 --> 00:05:24,057
Long time.

99
00:05:24,090 --> 00:05:28,761
Need to see ya.

100
00:05:28,795 --> 00:05:30,630
Yeah.

101
00:05:30,663 --> 00:05:36,002
[light polka music]

102
00:05:36,035 --> 00:05:39,005
[Rudolph, the Red-Nosed
Reindeer
 playing]

103
00:05:39,038 --> 00:05:46,979
♪

104
00:06:14,474 --> 00:06:17,009
(woman)
All right, everybody,
and here we go.

105
00:06:17,043 --> 00:06:19,679
Mary the Blaster is back.

106
00:06:19,712 --> 00:06:20,680
[scattered applause]

107
00:06:20,713 --> 00:06:22,882
All right.

108
00:06:22,915 --> 00:06:25,618
Blast is the name,
and Blast is the game.

109
00:06:25,651 --> 00:06:27,854
Four days to Christmas,
everyone.

110
00:06:27,887 --> 00:06:28,721
Unbelievable.

111
00:06:28,755 --> 00:06:30,590
And I have
one of my favorites here:

112
00:06:30,623 --> 00:06:33,793
Tony and the Desert Kings
honkin' your way.

113
00:06:33,826 --> 00:06:35,161
[scattered applause]

114
00:06:35,194 --> 00:06:37,663
[O Come, All Ye Faithful intro]

115
00:06:37,697 --> 00:06:40,066
[music warbles]

116
00:06:40,099 --> 00:06:44,103
Okay, don't stop dancing!

117
00:06:44,137 --> 00:06:51,010
[people murmuring]

118
00:06:51,043 --> 00:06:53,012
[cheers and applause]

119
00:06:53,045 --> 00:06:57,216
[music resumes]

120
00:06:57,250 --> 00:07:00,219
[record scratches]

121
00:07:04,056 --> 00:07:07,493
All right, Christmas 2000,
everybody sing with me.

122
00:07:07,527 --> 00:07:12,165
(all)
♪ O come, all ye faithful,

123
00:07:12,198 --> 00:07:16,169
♪ joyful and triumphant.

124
00:07:16,202 --> 00:07:20,273
♪ O come, ye,
O come, ye, to Bethlehem. ♪

125
00:07:20,306 --> 00:07:23,176
[Mary's voice]
Hail Mary, full of grace.
The Lord is with thee.

126
00:07:23,209 --> 00:07:25,511
Blessed art thou amongst women,
and blessed is--

127
00:07:25,545 --> 00:07:29,549
♪ Come and behold Him,

128
00:07:29,582 --> 00:07:33,586
♪ born the king of angels.

129
00:07:33,619 --> 00:07:34,787
(Mary)
Joy to the world.

130
00:07:34,821 --> 00:07:38,157
(all)
♪ O come, let us adore Him.

131
00:07:38,191 --> 00:07:42,695
♪ O come, let us adore Him.

132
00:07:42,728 --> 00:07:47,700
♪ O come, let us adore Him,

133
00:07:47,733 --> 00:07:51,871
♪ Christ, the Lord.  ♪

134
00:07:51,904 --> 00:07:53,773
[fireworks crackling]

135
00:07:53,806 --> 00:07:56,776
[cheers and whistles]

136
00:07:56,809 --> 00:08:00,079
[fireworks whooshing]

137
00:08:04,684 --> 00:08:07,620
[panting and coughing]

138
00:08:08,821 --> 00:08:10,656
Which way?
Which way? Which way?

139
00:08:10,690 --> 00:08:13,993
[fireworks exploding]

140
00:08:14,026 --> 00:08:14,994
Yeah.

141
00:08:15,027 --> 00:08:16,896
Mary the Blast.

142
00:08:20,967 --> 00:08:25,004
[whispering]
You meant
the world to me, Daddy.

143
00:08:25,037 --> 00:08:26,839
What's that, baby?

144
00:08:26,873 --> 00:08:30,910
You meant the world
to me, Daddy.

145
00:08:37,383 --> 00:08:39,552
(man)
She's gone, sir.

146
00:08:43,656 --> 00:08:45,591
Please.

147
00:09:11,350 --> 00:09:14,954
[Mary humming]

148
00:09:18,291 --> 00:09:19,792
Mary.

149
00:09:19,825 --> 00:09:20,760
[humming stops]

150
00:09:27,667 --> 00:09:28,668
Go to hell, Jacques.

151
00:09:28,701 --> 00:09:30,803
I need your help,
for real.

152
00:09:30,836 --> 00:09:31,804
You--you got to take me

153
00:09:31,837 --> 00:09:34,206
to the American border
very quickly, please.

154
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:38,277
[engine revving]

155
00:09:38,311 --> 00:09:41,414
Man, trouble still follows you
like a horny dog, doesn't it?

156
00:09:41,447 --> 00:09:43,115
(Jacques)
Oh, shit.

157
00:09:52,224 --> 00:09:55,194
[Mary humming]

158
00:09:55,227 --> 00:09:58,164
[men humming]

159
00:10:07,239 --> 00:10:08,207
[chimes tinkling]

160
00:10:08,240 --> 00:10:09,208
Hello?

161
00:10:09,241 --> 00:10:11,210
Blaster.

162
00:10:14,747 --> 00:10:17,383
Whew.

163
00:10:17,416 --> 00:10:18,718
I know you.

164
00:10:18,751 --> 00:10:22,221
You were up at Cordobes'
last Easter.

165
00:10:22,254 --> 00:10:23,222
You're Chollo,
right?

166
00:10:23,255 --> 00:10:25,157
Mm-hmm,
that's right.

167
00:10:25,191 --> 00:10:30,062
Well, Blaster, we're out here
lookin' for a goddamn fool.

168
00:10:30,096 --> 00:10:32,164
You, uh, seen any?

169
00:10:32,198 --> 00:10:34,166
[chuckles]
Come on, now.

170
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:35,201
I hate fools.

171
00:10:35,234 --> 00:10:37,203
Yeah, well,
this ain't any old fool.

172
00:10:37,236 --> 00:10:42,341
This here's that flimsy
little French fool, Jacques.

173
00:10:42,375 --> 00:10:44,176
We heard he was headed
this way.

174
00:10:44,210 --> 00:10:46,746
(Mary)
Yeah?
What you want with him?

175
00:10:46,779 --> 00:10:50,750
Oh, Mr. Cordobes would like
to talk to him is all.

176
00:10:50,783 --> 00:10:53,019
Mr. Cordobes?

177
00:10:53,052 --> 00:10:55,988
You tell Mr. Cordobes

178
00:10:56,022 --> 00:10:58,290
that if I bump
into any fools,

179
00:10:58,324 --> 00:11:00,159
especially French ones,

180
00:11:00,192 --> 00:11:02,361
I'll give him a call.

181
00:11:08,367 --> 00:11:10,403
While you're at it, uh,

182
00:11:10,436 --> 00:11:13,873
why don't you give me
a call too?

183
00:11:13,906 --> 00:11:15,141
A little bit later.

184
00:11:15,174 --> 00:11:18,944
I'd like to show you
what a man like me can do

185
00:11:18,978 --> 00:11:21,514
to a, uh, girl like you.

186
00:11:21,547 --> 00:11:27,086
Phone sex with a chainsaw
doesn't turn me on, Chollo.

187
00:11:27,119 --> 00:11:29,422
Yeah, well,
I never quite knew

188
00:11:29,455 --> 00:11:33,893
what the boss saw good
in you anyhow, Blaster.

189
00:11:43,536 --> 00:11:44,503
[kissing noises]

190
00:11:44,537 --> 00:11:47,273
Come on.

191
00:11:47,306 --> 00:11:51,277
[humming]
[whistling]

192
00:11:55,414 --> 00:11:58,384
[engine revs]

193
00:12:17,870 --> 00:12:18,938
Cordobes?

194
00:12:18,971 --> 00:12:21,107
What are you, crazy?

195
00:12:21,140 --> 00:12:24,076
That old skull,
he's disgusting.

196
00:12:24,110 --> 00:12:26,979
He scared me last Easter
just looking at him.

197
00:12:27,012 --> 00:12:28,948
Boy, did you ever mess with
the wrong joker.

198
00:12:28,981 --> 00:12:31,884
I don't understand
what's happened.

199
00:12:31,917 --> 00:12:34,220
I was just playing at
bullfighting at Cordobes' place,

200
00:12:34,253 --> 00:12:37,156
and next, I don't know.

201
00:12:37,189 --> 00:12:39,125
Laila let Diablo out.

202
00:12:39,158 --> 00:12:41,393
That kid, Laila?

203
00:12:41,427 --> 00:12:43,195
She turned that killer on you?

204
00:12:43,229 --> 00:12:44,930
She said,
"Like you always say,

205
00:12:44,964 --> 00:12:46,398
if you love me, show me."

206
00:12:46,432 --> 00:12:48,000
W-w-w-wait a second.

207
00:12:48,033 --> 00:12:51,403
You were courting
Cordobes' kid?

208
00:12:51,437 --> 00:12:53,506
And you used
that dumb phony line on her?

209
00:12:53,539 --> 00:12:58,410
Mary, it was a real bull,
understand?

210
00:12:58,444 --> 00:13:00,479
And the bull turned

211
00:13:00,513 --> 00:13:03,949
and gored her.

212
00:13:03,983 --> 00:13:05,551
Would I make that up?

213
00:13:10,489 --> 00:13:12,091
I don't think she
was hurt too bad.

214
00:13:12,124 --> 00:13:14,493
No.

215
00:13:14,527 --> 00:13:15,494
And she told me to run.

216
00:13:15,528 --> 00:13:16,495
It was not my idea.

217
00:13:16,529 --> 00:13:18,898
She told me!

218
00:13:18,931 --> 00:13:21,100
[chuckles]

219
00:13:21,133 --> 00:13:22,535
Amazing.

220
00:13:22,568 --> 00:13:23,936
[sighs]

221
00:13:23,969 --> 00:13:26,205
You're always
the victim.

222
00:13:29,341 --> 00:13:34,113
(man)
From the book of Wisdom,
chapter 3, verses 1 through 9.

223
00:13:34,146 --> 00:13:37,149
"The souls of the just
are in the hand of God,

224
00:13:37,183 --> 00:13:39,919
"and no torment
shall touch them.

225
00:13:39,952 --> 00:13:41,987
[car engine revs]

226
00:13:42,021 --> 00:13:44,890
"They seemed, in the view
of the foolish, to be dead,

227
00:13:44,924 --> 00:13:46,592
but they are in peace."

228
00:13:46,625 --> 00:13:51,197
St. Paul's first letter
to Corinthians,

229
00:13:51,230 --> 00:13:55,401
chapter 15,
verses 51 through 57.

230
00:13:55,434 --> 00:13:57,136
"Behold,

231
00:13:57,169 --> 00:14:00,606
"I tell you a mystery.

232
00:14:00,639 --> 00:14:02,608
"We shall not all
fall asleep,

233
00:14:02,641 --> 00:14:06,645
"but we shall be changed
in an instant,

234
00:14:06,679 --> 00:14:09,381
"in the blink of an eye,

235
00:14:09,415 --> 00:14:11,483
"at the last trumpet,

236
00:14:11,517 --> 00:14:15,387
"for this
which is corruptible

237
00:14:15,421 --> 00:14:18,657
"must clothe itself
with incorruptibility,

238
00:14:18,691 --> 00:14:21,126
"and that which is mortal

239
00:14:21,160 --> 00:14:24,129
"must clothe itself
with immortability.

240
00:14:24,163 --> 00:14:27,933
"Then it shall be
brought to pass

241
00:14:27,967 --> 00:14:29,268
the saying
that is written"--

242
00:14:29,301 --> 00:14:30,502
[door creaking]

243
00:14:30,536 --> 00:14:34,440
♪ I said-a, "Hey, ho,
and that-- ♪

244
00:14:36,308 --> 00:14:37,576
(man)
"And where,
O death"--

245
00:14:37,610 --> 00:14:39,945
Thank you, Padre.

246
00:14:39,979 --> 00:14:43,649
Amen.

247
00:14:43,682 --> 00:14:46,652
I ain't seen my old partner
in 15 years.

248
00:14:46,685 --> 00:14:48,354
Ring, ring,
he calls me,

249
00:14:48,387 --> 00:14:50,556
only to invite me
to a funeral.

250
00:14:50,589 --> 00:14:51,991
That's my daughter, Jones.

251
00:14:52,024 --> 00:14:55,027
[sighs]

252
00:14:55,060 --> 00:14:56,028
Sorry, I, uh--

253
00:14:56,061 --> 00:14:59,265
I mean, uh,
what happened?

254
00:14:59,298 --> 00:15:00,266
Last night,

255
00:15:00,299 --> 00:15:07,106
gored by the bull.

256
00:15:07,139 --> 00:15:09,475
Doesn't make any sense.

257
00:15:09,508 --> 00:15:13,045
Scared to death
of that bull.

258
00:15:13,078 --> 00:15:17,349
I believe she was pushed
or baited.

259
00:15:25,024 --> 00:15:30,529
She is--she was--
she is beautiful.

260
00:15:30,562 --> 00:15:33,532
So was her mama.

261
00:15:40,572 --> 00:15:42,741
We lost her
a long time ago.

262
00:15:42,775 --> 00:15:46,512
When Allison died,

263
00:15:46,545 --> 00:15:50,082
I said I'd spoil her.

264
00:15:50,115 --> 00:15:53,052
I probably did
a little bit.

265
00:15:53,085 --> 00:15:55,688
But she had the devil in her.

266
00:15:55,721 --> 00:16:00,492
She was doing things
behind my back.

267
00:16:02,761 --> 00:16:05,531
I'm so goddamn tired.

268
00:16:05,564 --> 00:16:07,633
I'm sorry

269
00:16:07,666 --> 00:16:10,102
that it got this bad.

270
00:16:10,135 --> 00:16:12,237
Anything you need...

271
00:16:12,271 --> 00:16:16,408
I need your talent.

272
00:16:16,442 --> 00:16:18,477
I fill you in
on that son of a bitch.

273
00:16:18,510 --> 00:16:20,379
You just track him

274
00:16:20,412 --> 00:16:22,214
and bring him back to me.

275
00:16:22,247 --> 00:16:26,185
You got it.

276
00:16:31,657 --> 00:16:32,591
[Cordobes muttering]

277
00:16:41,467 --> 00:16:43,435
Look out.

278
00:16:58,717 --> 00:17:01,720
[coyote howling]

279
00:17:01,754 --> 00:17:03,222
[static hissing]

280
00:17:03,255 --> 00:17:06,425
[Mary yawning]
Yeah, the radio
doesn't work all the time.

281
00:17:06,458 --> 00:17:07,626
Aw.

282
00:17:07,659 --> 00:17:09,294
(woman)
♪ And an angel's kiss--

283
00:17:09,328 --> 00:17:11,563
Ah,Summer Wine.

284
00:17:11,597 --> 00:17:13,632
This song is a poem.

285
00:17:13,665 --> 00:17:15,033
[laughing]

286
00:17:15,067 --> 00:17:20,572
[singing along]
♪ Summer wine is really made
for all these things. ♪

287
00:17:20,606 --> 00:17:24,743
[clapping rhythmically]

288
00:17:24,777 --> 00:17:27,146
♪

289
00:17:27,179 --> 00:17:29,148
[singing along]
♪ I walked in town

290
00:17:29,181 --> 00:17:32,551
♪ on silver spurs
that jingled to-- ♪

291
00:17:32,584 --> 00:17:33,852
[both chuckling]

292
00:17:33,886 --> 00:17:34,853
Come on, sing.

293
00:17:34,887 --> 00:17:36,288
I don't know
the line after.

294
00:17:36,321 --> 00:17:37,289
[laughing]

295
00:17:37,322 --> 00:17:40,292
[humming]

296
00:17:40,325 --> 00:17:43,695
(man)
♪ She saw my silver spurs--

297
00:17:43,729 --> 00:17:45,764
(Mary) 
♪
And helped me pass
the time--
♪

298
00:17:45,798 --> 00:17:47,466
Da-da-da-da-da-da.

299
00:17:47,499 --> 00:17:50,302
♪ And I will give
to you-- ♪

300
00:17:50,335 --> 00:17:53,372
(both)
♪ Summer wine.

301
00:17:53,405 --> 00:17:58,177
♪ Ooh-ooh, ooh,
summer wine. ♪

302
00:17:58,210 --> 00:18:00,913
(Mary)
But I'm dropping you in El Paso.

303
00:18:00,946 --> 00:18:02,548
I'm gonna have to make a stop.

304
00:18:02,581 --> 00:18:04,416
I got a gig up in San Miguel
tomorrow night,

305
00:18:04,450 --> 00:18:05,417
and I am not missing it.

306
00:18:05,451 --> 00:18:07,453
[van creaking]

307
00:18:07,486 --> 00:18:08,454
[groans]

308
00:18:08,487 --> 00:18:10,289
(woman)
♪ My summer wine is...

309
00:18:10,322 --> 00:18:11,557
Would you let me see
your arm?

310
00:18:11,590 --> 00:18:14,159
(woman)
♪ ...made from
all these things. ♪

311
00:18:14,193 --> 00:18:16,261
Ay!

312
00:18:16,295 --> 00:18:17,696
[groans]
Oh, that's infected.

313
00:18:17,729 --> 00:18:20,466
Okay,
you need stitches.

314
00:18:20,499 --> 00:18:22,568
You're nothing
but trouble.

315
00:18:22,601 --> 00:18:26,872
Uh, there's a doctor
up in San Miguel, I think.

316
00:18:26,905 --> 00:18:28,373
[phone beeping]

317
00:18:28,407 --> 00:18:30,175
If this thing
doesn't keep cutting off.

318
00:18:30,209 --> 00:18:31,310
(woman)
♪ Summer wine.  ♪

319
00:18:31,343 --> 00:18:32,311
[explosion rumbling]

320
00:18:32,344 --> 00:18:34,379
What was that?

321
00:18:34,413 --> 00:18:39,418
[booming and whooshing sounds]

322
00:18:53,799 --> 00:18:54,900
(woman)
Jacques?

323
00:18:54,933 --> 00:18:57,202
Your planet, Earth.

324
00:18:57,236 --> 00:19:00,305
The universal evil
is encircling pure good.

325
00:19:00,339 --> 00:19:03,275
You must wake up!

326
00:19:03,308 --> 00:19:06,845
That's why the Messiah
comes now--comes now.

327
00:19:06,879 --> 00:19:11,950
The Messiah will arrive
in precisely 72 hours.

328
00:19:11,984 --> 00:19:16,321
An extinctor comes to hunt down
and kill the Messiah!

329
00:19:16,355 --> 00:19:19,925
You, Jacques,
must prevent this.

330
00:19:19,958 --> 00:19:21,727
I'm always
helping you.

331
00:19:21,760 --> 00:19:24,296
This is
your last chance.

332
00:19:24,329 --> 00:19:27,266
[sizzling sound]

333
00:19:35,507 --> 00:19:37,743
You'll meet a soldier
who waits to give you a book.

334
00:19:37,776 --> 00:19:38,911
Check your wound next time.

335
00:19:38,944 --> 00:19:41,613
You'll see what is real.

336
00:19:41,647 --> 00:19:43,315
[horn blaring]

337
00:19:43,348 --> 00:19:44,516
(Mary)
Jacques!

338
00:19:44,550 --> 00:19:45,584
Jacques!

339
00:19:45,617 --> 00:19:46,718
Jacques!
Jacques!

340
00:19:46,752 --> 00:19:48,820
Jacques!
Jacques, wake up!

341
00:19:48,854 --> 00:19:49,855
Wake up!

342
00:19:49,888 --> 00:19:50,856
Jacques!

343
00:19:50,889 --> 00:19:52,024
[tires squealing]

344
00:19:52,057 --> 00:19:53,659
[metal clanking]

345
00:20:01,366 --> 00:20:02,668
Did you hear that?

346
00:20:02,701 --> 00:20:04,403
Hear what?

347
00:20:04,436 --> 00:20:06,405
The bell.

348
00:20:06,438 --> 00:20:08,941
How the hell?

349
00:20:08,974 --> 00:20:10,842
How the---

350
00:20:20,352 --> 00:20:23,822
Gomez?

351
00:20:23,855 --> 00:20:26,825
How the hell
did we get here?

352
00:20:26,858 --> 00:20:29,394
Where--what,
did I sleep all night?

353
00:20:29,428 --> 00:20:32,497
[breathing heavily]

354
00:20:32,531 --> 00:20:35,434
We're 300 miles
from where we started.

355
00:20:44,042 --> 00:20:46,912
Come on, guy,
this is Christmastimes.

356
00:20:50,015 --> 00:20:52,851
I want to see
Santa Claus is Coming to Town.

357
00:20:55,821 --> 00:20:58,757
[water dripping]

358
00:21:05,764 --> 00:21:07,566
Check your wound next time.

359
00:21:12,938 --> 00:21:13,705
Mary, maybe the most--

360
00:21:13,739 --> 00:21:17,876
Maybe I am taking
a shower...alone.

361
00:21:17,909 --> 00:21:18,977
Out!

362
00:21:19,011 --> 00:21:19,978
Jacques.

363
00:21:20,012 --> 00:21:20,979
[sighs]

364
00:21:21,013 --> 00:21:23,915
Just go to sleep.

365
00:21:23,949 --> 00:21:27,352
You have to rest
until we get your arm fixed.

366
00:21:27,386 --> 00:21:30,055
No, my arm,
it's different now.

367
00:21:30,088 --> 00:21:32,958
Did you get
the big picture here?

368
00:21:32,991 --> 00:21:34,559
I shower,
and you sleep.

369
00:21:34,593 --> 00:21:35,661
Then we go find
a doctor.

370
00:21:35,694 --> 00:21:37,829
All right?
Now, get out.

371
00:21:37,863 --> 00:21:38,830
Touch.

372
00:21:38,864 --> 00:21:40,932
What's wrong
with this?

373
00:21:40,966 --> 00:21:43,135
Nothing.

374
00:21:43,168 --> 00:21:45,103
Nothing.

375
00:21:45,137 --> 00:21:46,538
What I thought.

376
00:21:46,571 --> 00:21:50,609
Just checking.

377
00:21:50,642 --> 00:21:52,144
When you finish
your shower,

378
00:21:52,177 --> 00:21:54,746
no doctor needed.

379
00:21:54,780 --> 00:21:56,782
Got to keep going through
to San Miguel.

380
00:21:58,984 --> 00:22:01,987
[mellow reggae music]

381
00:22:02,020 --> 00:22:09,961
♪

382
00:22:16,535 --> 00:22:17,936
You okay?

383
00:22:21,506 --> 00:22:23,108
Can I see your arm again?

384
00:22:26,511 --> 00:22:28,380
You want to talk
about your arm?

385
00:22:31,483 --> 00:22:32,851
Well, what's up with that?

386
00:22:35,087 --> 00:22:36,988
What, is it the shower?
Did I piss you off?

387
00:22:37,022 --> 00:22:39,057
No, no, you're helping me.
Thanks.

388
00:22:39,091 --> 00:22:42,160
You know, we're gonna be
locked up in this tin can

389
00:22:42,194 --> 00:22:43,662
for the next couple of days.

390
00:22:43,695 --> 00:22:45,197
You might as well spit it out.

391
00:22:45,230 --> 00:22:48,200
[man singing in Spanish]

392
00:22:48,233 --> 00:22:53,572
♪

393
00:22:53,605 --> 00:22:55,474
I had a vision.

394
00:22:55,507 --> 00:22:57,776
An angel lady spoke to me

395
00:22:57,809 --> 00:22:59,478
about protecting
the future world.

396
00:22:59,511 --> 00:23:00,479
Shit!

397
00:23:00,512 --> 00:23:03,515
[tires squealing]

398
00:23:18,997 --> 00:23:22,100
Would somebody like to tell me
why I'm saving his crazy ass?

399
00:23:22,134 --> 00:23:24,102
Hey, remember that big light?

400
00:23:24,136 --> 00:23:25,337
Hitting us off the road?

401
00:23:25,370 --> 00:23:28,206
I remember you driving straight
into that 18-wheel truck.

402
00:23:28,240 --> 00:23:30,108
No, no, before that,
when we were singing.

403
00:23:30,142 --> 00:23:31,810
Singin'?
Yeah.

404
00:23:31,843 --> 00:23:35,080
Then bam!
There she was.

405
00:23:35,113 --> 00:23:39,151
Angel lady.

406
00:23:39,184 --> 00:23:40,619
She said
I'm on a mission.

407
00:23:40,652 --> 00:23:41,620
Mm-hmm.

408
00:23:41,653 --> 00:23:45,190
Protecting some Messiah guy
from the underworld.

409
00:23:45,223 --> 00:23:46,892
But she'll be helping me.

410
00:23:46,925 --> 00:23:48,760
Okay, Jacques--
No, no,
let me finish.

411
00:23:48,794 --> 00:23:50,662
Anyway, I don't think
I start this mission

412
00:23:50,695 --> 00:23:51,496
till tomorrow night

413
00:23:51,530 --> 00:23:53,765
because that's when
the Messiah comes.

414
00:23:53,799 --> 00:23:56,168
Hmm.

415
00:23:56,201 --> 00:23:58,236
You doin' a lot
of drugs, Jacques?

416
00:23:58,270 --> 00:24:03,041
Talking to her was as real
as talking to you now.

417
00:24:03,074 --> 00:24:04,843
Really?

418
00:24:04,876 --> 00:24:07,179
Actually,
more real.

419
00:24:07,212 --> 00:24:09,514
What?

420
00:24:09,548 --> 00:24:11,917
You're--you're fighting me
about this?

421
00:24:11,950 --> 00:24:12,717
You?

422
00:24:12,751 --> 00:24:14,619
But you believe
in all these things.

423
00:24:14,653 --> 00:24:16,922
You know, um,
how do you say that in English?

424
00:24:16,955 --> 00:24:18,089
Religion stuff.

425
00:24:18,123 --> 00:24:20,058
Religion stuff?

426
00:24:21,326 --> 00:24:23,528
Right.

427
00:24:23,562 --> 00:24:25,630
Okay, there's one thing
I don't get, Jacques.

428
00:24:25,664 --> 00:24:30,168
You don't believe
in God, right?

429
00:24:30,202 --> 00:24:33,038
You have never set foot
in a church.

430
00:24:33,071 --> 00:24:34,039
Right?

431
00:24:34,072 --> 00:24:35,774
And...

432
00:24:35,807 --> 00:24:39,978
you're a pagan loser.

433
00:24:40,011 --> 00:24:42,914
So this mission...

434
00:24:42,948 --> 00:24:45,784
why you, Jacques, huh?

435
00:24:45,817 --> 00:24:47,953
Why you?

436
00:24:52,958 --> 00:24:57,162
Maybe I need
this shot.

437
00:24:57,195 --> 00:25:01,900
She said this is
my last chance.

438
00:25:01,933 --> 00:25:05,770
For redemption, I guess.

439
00:25:05,804 --> 00:25:08,640
Jacques, you got
no chance.

440
00:25:08,673 --> 00:25:09,975
And no angels
talk to jerks.

441
00:25:10,008 --> 00:25:12,544
Angels don't like jerks.

442
00:25:15,680 --> 00:25:16,681
So who fixed my arm?

443
00:25:22,687 --> 00:25:24,656
Maybe it wasn't as bad
as it seemed.

444
00:25:24,689 --> 00:25:29,127
♪

445
00:25:29,160 --> 00:25:30,595
[tires squeal]

446
00:25:30,629 --> 00:25:38,570
♪

447
00:25:59,057 --> 00:26:02,994
[sirens wailing]

448
00:26:08,867 --> 00:26:11,136
Jones, get your fuckin' ass
in gear!

449
00:26:13,071 --> 00:26:16,408
We're running behind!

450
00:26:16,441 --> 00:26:22,247
[eerie music]

451
00:26:22,280 --> 00:26:24,015
Daddy?

452
00:26:24,049 --> 00:26:25,383
[tires squealing]

453
00:26:25,417 --> 00:26:28,720
[sirens wailing]

454
00:26:28,753 --> 00:26:29,821
They're gone for now.

455
00:26:32,123 --> 00:26:34,025
(Cordobes)
Laila.

456
00:26:34,059 --> 00:26:35,393
I miss you,
Daddy.

457
00:26:35,427 --> 00:26:37,262
Will you do your little girl
a favor?

458
00:26:37,295 --> 00:26:38,863
Come with me.
[giggling]

459
00:26:38,897 --> 00:26:41,132
[man grunting]

460
00:26:41,166 --> 00:26:42,200
[gasping]

461
00:26:42,233 --> 00:26:44,369
(man)
This can't be real.

462
00:26:44,402 --> 00:26:45,737
No?

463
00:26:45,770 --> 00:26:48,807
Did you think maybe
it's the movie?

464
00:26:48,840 --> 00:26:49,975
Know what I say?

465
00:26:50,008 --> 00:26:52,744
I say, if the movie
don't have Elvis in it,

466
00:26:52,777 --> 00:26:54,012
it ain't worth a damn.

467
00:26:54,045 --> 00:26:56,915
(Laila)
They can't see
or hear you, Daddy.

468
00:26:56,948 --> 00:26:58,683
[piano keys play discordantly]

469
00:26:58,717 --> 00:27:01,820
A little, uh,
thinkin' music for ya.

470
00:27:01,853 --> 00:27:03,154
[snaps fingers]

471
00:27:03,188 --> 00:27:06,324
[plays discordant glissando]

472
00:27:06,358 --> 00:27:07,792
[playing
Chopsticks]

473
00:27:07,826 --> 00:27:09,861
Jones, you lying
son of a bitch.

474
00:27:09,894 --> 00:27:11,029
He got caught
in the vault.

475
00:27:11,062 --> 00:27:12,130
He jumped
into the vault.

476
00:27:12,163 --> 00:27:13,732
He shoot
to protect himself.

477
00:27:13,765 --> 00:27:14,766
Couldn't get the money.

478
00:27:14,799 --> 00:27:15,767
Had to run out.

479
00:27:15,800 --> 00:27:17,469
[shouting]
Lying son of a bitch!

480
00:27:17,502 --> 00:27:19,037
I had to show you, Daddy.

481
00:27:19,070 --> 00:27:20,271
Give him some air.

482
00:27:20,305 --> 00:27:24,342
Now, you know, it only takes
telling me eight little numbers,

483
00:27:24,376 --> 00:27:25,810
and he'll breathe.

484
00:27:25,844 --> 00:27:26,811
Elvis, huh?

485
00:27:26,845 --> 00:27:28,179
I'm beggin' you.

486
00:27:28,213 --> 00:27:29,381
(Jones)
You're what?

487
00:27:29,414 --> 00:27:30,382
Tell me numbers.

488
00:27:30,415 --> 00:27:32,450
[cackling]

489
00:27:32,484 --> 00:27:34,953
You laughin'?

490
00:27:34,986 --> 00:27:37,989
Laughin' at my Elvis
piano playin'?

491
00:27:38,023 --> 00:27:39,357
[shouts]
No! No!

492
00:27:39,391 --> 00:27:42,961
[keys banging]

493
00:27:42,994 --> 00:27:46,798
[sighs]

494
00:27:53,371 --> 00:27:57,342
[Chopsticks
 continues]

495
00:27:57,375 --> 00:28:04,149
I'll, uh, give him some air.

496
00:28:04,182 --> 00:28:06,751
[gunshot]

497
00:28:06,785 --> 00:28:09,020
[whimpering]

498
00:28:09,054 --> 00:28:10,755
Sweet air.

499
00:28:10,789 --> 00:28:12,824
No.
Goddamn you!

500
00:28:12,857 --> 00:28:15,527
[grunting]

501
00:28:15,560 --> 00:28:16,961
[groaning]

502
00:28:16,995 --> 00:28:18,096
[plastic whooshing]

503
00:28:18,129 --> 00:28:19,097
No.

504
00:28:33,445 --> 00:28:35,814
8-6-7...

505
00:28:35,847 --> 00:28:37,916
Come on.

506
00:28:37,949 --> 00:28:38,950
Give me the rest of it.

507
00:28:40,985 --> 00:28:41,953
Unh!

508
00:28:41,986 --> 00:28:42,954
Come on.

509
00:28:42,987 --> 00:28:43,955
Uh--

510
00:28:43,988 --> 00:28:46,291
[sighs]

511
00:28:46,324 --> 00:28:49,227
8-6-7-5-3-0-9-1.

512
00:28:49,260 --> 00:28:52,530
Gee, thank you, Colonel.

513
00:28:54,165 --> 00:28:56,167
Ah!

514
00:28:56,201 --> 00:28:58,436
No!

515
00:29:00,205 --> 00:29:02,874
[grunts]

516
00:29:02,907 --> 00:29:05,877
[humming]

517
00:29:05,910 --> 00:29:08,880
8-6-7--
ah, God damn it.

518
00:29:08,913 --> 00:29:12,317
8-6-7-5-what?

519
00:29:12,350 --> 00:29:15,086
(man)
3-0-9-1.

520
00:29:15,120 --> 00:29:16,988
Appreciate that.

521
00:29:18,890 --> 00:29:22,827
Look at that sneaky little
son of a bitch.

522
00:29:22,861 --> 00:29:25,897
Money in the safe
belonged to Ronnie the Dog.

523
00:29:25,930 --> 00:29:27,332
The cops
were supposed to get it,

524
00:29:27,365 --> 00:29:28,433
get a kickback.

525
00:29:28,466 --> 00:29:31,469
You rotten, dirty, little wormy
son of a bitch.

526
00:29:31,503 --> 00:29:32,570
If I'd have known
at the time,

527
00:29:32,604 --> 00:29:37,242
I'd have blown a goddamn hole
in his ass a mile wide,

528
00:29:37,275 --> 00:29:39,177
given the money back
to Ronnie the Dog,

529
00:29:39,210 --> 00:29:41,146
and never have to go
to Mexico.

530
00:29:44,015 --> 00:29:45,950
You've been running
17 years,

531
00:29:45,984 --> 00:29:48,853
my whole life.

532
00:29:48,887 --> 00:29:49,988
Ah, baby.

533
00:29:50,021 --> 00:29:51,322
Obliged to you all.

534
00:29:51,356 --> 00:29:54,959
Thank you
for a fine performance.

535
00:29:54,993 --> 00:29:55,960
No.

536
00:29:55,994 --> 00:29:57,295
And now
the fat lady sings.

537
00:29:57,328 --> 00:29:58,596
[man screams]
No!

538
00:29:58,630 --> 00:30:01,466
[gunshots]

539
00:30:01,499 --> 00:30:06,137
[wheezing]

