01:01:06,095 --> 01:01:07,296
I'll take care of you.

1086
01:01:07,330 --> 01:01:08,498
Jacques, you don't even know

1087
01:01:08,531 --> 01:01:10,967
if you're going to be alive
tomorrow.

1088
01:02:05,455 --> 01:02:08,391
Why are you doing this to me?

1089
01:02:13,129 --> 01:02:16,065
Why are you putting me
through this?

1090
01:02:18,401 --> 01:02:21,370
I want to know.

1091
01:02:25,208 --> 01:02:26,943
You know I tried
going straight once.

1092
01:02:26,976 --> 01:02:29,479
You know that.

1093
01:02:29,512 --> 01:02:32,482
But you weren't there.

1094
01:02:35,551 --> 01:02:40,256
You're never there...

1095
01:02:40,289 --> 01:02:43,259
when people need you the most.

1096
01:02:52,268 --> 01:02:56,038
You took the only thing
that meant anything to me.

1097
01:02:56,072 --> 01:02:58,107
Wasn't that enough?

1098
01:02:58,141 --> 01:03:00,510
Now you take little Laila?

1099
01:03:00,543 --> 01:03:04,947
I don't think you ever existed.

1100
01:03:10,153 --> 01:03:13,122
Say something.

1101
01:03:20,029 --> 01:03:21,264
(Laila)
I know where they are.

1102
01:03:27,270 --> 01:03:29,372
If we are lucky,

1103
01:03:29,405 --> 01:03:33,876
we can find some diner
for Christmas turkey somewhere.

1104
01:03:33,910 --> 01:03:34,777
You feel okay?

1105
01:03:34,810 --> 01:03:39,649
Jacques, I don't think
I can walk anymore.

1106
01:03:39,682 --> 01:03:42,885
My feet and my hands
are all swollen up.

1107
01:03:42,919 --> 01:03:44,887
No problem.

1108
01:03:45,955 --> 01:03:47,456
Take a seat.

1109
01:03:52,128 --> 01:03:53,229
What are you do--

1110
01:03:53,262 --> 01:03:54,230
no, no, please don't.

1111
01:03:54,263 --> 01:03:58,134
My feet stink, Jacques.

1112
01:03:58,167 --> 01:04:00,469
Better now?

1113
01:04:05,308 --> 01:04:07,109
How's the baby inside?

1114
01:04:07,143 --> 01:04:09,145
I think I need tomatoes.

1115
01:04:09,178 --> 01:04:12,481
I remember my mother,

1116
01:04:12,515 --> 01:04:17,253
she told me
that, um, Dr. Spock,

1117
01:04:17,286 --> 01:04:21,557
he said that pregnant women
are supposed to eat tomatoes

1118
01:04:21,591 --> 01:04:25,494
when it's over 90 degrees
in the shade, you know, so...

1119
01:04:25,528 --> 01:04:27,129
Jacques,
what if it's dying?

1120
01:04:27,163 --> 01:04:28,998
What if it's dying?

1121
01:04:34,370 --> 01:04:38,140
Nobody's dying, okay?

1122
01:04:41,978 --> 01:04:45,615
Maybe we can flag down a plane.

1123
01:04:45,648 --> 01:04:47,116
[engine backfires]

1124
01:04:47,149 --> 01:04:49,518
[man laughing heartily]

1125
01:04:49,552 --> 01:04:51,487
Is that real?

1126
01:04:51,520 --> 01:04:53,723
[man shouting]

1127
01:04:53,756 --> 01:04:56,192
Much nicer
than a mirage.

1128
01:05:28,557 --> 01:05:29,525
Hey, hey!

1129
01:05:29,558 --> 01:05:32,261
Whoa!
Whoa!

1130
01:05:32,295 --> 01:05:34,030
[shouting indistinctly]

1131
01:05:34,063 --> 01:05:36,132
[laughing hysterically]

1132
01:05:36,165 --> 01:05:39,535
[gunshots]

1133
01:05:39,568 --> 01:05:41,470
Cordobes.

1134
01:05:41,504 --> 01:05:43,539
(Mary)
Jacques!

1135
01:05:43,572 --> 01:05:45,007
I beg your pardon.

1136
01:05:45,041 --> 01:05:47,143
(Mary)
It's kicking.

1137
01:05:47,176 --> 01:05:49,111
The baby's kicking hard!

1138
01:05:49,145 --> 01:05:50,112
(Jacques)
Get down.

1139
01:05:50,146 --> 01:05:51,180
No guns, Jacques.

1140
01:05:51,213 --> 01:05:52,782
(Jacques)
A guardian angel left it.

1141
01:05:52,815 --> 01:05:56,018
[gunshots]

1142
01:05:56,052 --> 01:05:57,787
[tires skidding]

1143
01:05:57,820 --> 01:05:59,388
Hold on.

1144
01:05:59,422 --> 01:06:00,489
[gunshots]

1145
01:06:00,523 --> 01:06:01,524
[Mary screaming]

1146
01:06:10,333 --> 01:06:11,300
[groans]

1147
01:06:11,334 --> 01:06:12,301
What?

1148
01:06:12,335 --> 01:06:13,135
What?

1149
01:06:13,169 --> 01:06:16,138
I think the contractions
have started.

1150
01:06:16,172 --> 01:06:17,440
Huh?

1151
01:06:17,473 --> 01:06:18,541
No, no,
it can't be right.

1152
01:06:18,574 --> 01:06:20,676
It is too early.

1153
01:06:20,710 --> 01:06:24,213
It's--it's--
it's not possible.

1154
01:06:24,246 --> 01:06:26,415
Oh, impossible?
Yeah?

1155
01:06:26,449 --> 01:06:28,718
Everything since I woke up
two days ago is impossible.

1156
01:06:28,751 --> 01:06:29,685
Oh!

1157
01:06:29,719 --> 01:06:32,088
[engine revving]

1158
01:06:35,558 --> 01:06:36,692
[harp glissando]

1159
01:06:40,429 --> 01:06:42,431
Run them down.

1160
01:06:42,465 --> 01:06:44,333
No, no.

1161
01:06:45,501 --> 01:06:47,636
I want to see the look
in Jacques' eyes

1162
01:06:47,670 --> 01:06:48,838
when I pull the trigger.

1163
01:06:48,871 --> 01:06:50,806
[giggles]
Yes, Daddy.

1164
01:06:50,840 --> 01:06:52,708
[giggling]

1165
01:06:56,612 --> 01:06:57,580
Damn it!

1166
01:06:57,613 --> 01:06:58,681
Hey, angel!

1167
01:06:58,714 --> 01:07:02,284
You said
you're always helping me.

1168
01:07:02,318 --> 01:07:03,786
Fuck I am supposed to do?

1169
01:07:03,819 --> 01:07:05,221
(Laila)
Gas.

1170
01:07:05,254 --> 01:07:07,223
(woman)
Jacques, use
the soldier's book.

1171
01:07:13,129 --> 01:07:14,330
Mary, get the book!

1172
01:07:23,305 --> 01:07:24,273
[gunshots]

1173
01:07:24,306 --> 01:07:26,742
[screaming]

1174
01:07:26,776 --> 01:07:29,245
What am I looking for?

1175
01:07:32,782 --> 01:07:34,650
Anything about
traveling or cars.

1176
01:07:34,683 --> 01:07:37,119
(Mary)
This isn't an Oldsmobile manual,
all right?

1177
01:07:37,153 --> 01:07:38,721
(Jacques)
Okay.

1178
01:07:42,825 --> 01:07:44,894
How to travel
in time or in space.

1179
01:07:44,927 --> 01:07:45,895
God damn it!

1180
01:07:45,928 --> 01:07:46,896
[gasping]

1181
01:07:46,929 --> 01:07:48,297
[spits]

1182
01:07:48,330 --> 01:07:49,698
[angrily]
Sit there.

1183
01:07:49,732 --> 01:07:51,400
Jacques,
do something, please.

1184
01:07:51,434 --> 01:07:54,503
[garbled voices on radio]

1185
01:07:54,537 --> 01:07:57,373
[organ music grinds down]

1186
01:07:57,406 --> 01:07:59,208
Yes, that's
what we did.

1187
01:07:59,241 --> 01:08:00,543
Mary, sing with me.

1188
01:08:00,576 --> 01:08:02,711
Close your eyes,
and block everything out.

1189
01:08:02,745 --> 01:08:03,813
Just listen to the tune.

1190
01:08:03,846 --> 01:08:05,481
I hate this song.
It's stupid.

1191
01:08:05,514 --> 01:08:06,849
Do it!
Do it!

1192
01:08:06,882 --> 01:08:08,484
Just do it, okay?
Deep and slow.

1193
01:08:08,517 --> 01:08:11,487
[groans]
♪ Should have married me.

1194
01:08:11,520 --> 01:08:12,655
Okay.

1195
01:08:12,688 --> 01:08:14,290
Keep concentrating
on the rhythm,

1196
01:08:14,323 --> 01:08:15,291
just the rhythm.

1197
01:08:15,324 --> 01:08:18,294
♪

1198
01:08:18,327 --> 01:08:23,365
[woman on radio]
♪ You used to run away
when you saw a road-- ♪

1199
01:08:23,399 --> 01:08:29,171
Right, what, hold on.

1200
01:08:29,205 --> 01:08:32,174
♪ Instead,
you should've married me. ♪

1201
01:08:32,208 --> 01:08:36,512
♪ Instead,
you should've married me. ♪

1202
01:08:36,545 --> 01:08:38,681
♪

1203
01:08:38,714 --> 01:08:44,353
♪ Instead of Elaine.

1204
01:08:44,386 --> 01:08:46,288
♪

1205
01:08:46,322 --> 01:08:50,259
♪ Instead of Elaine.  ♪

1206
01:08:53,429 --> 01:08:56,532
[Mary groans]

1207
01:08:58,801 --> 01:09:01,270
Jacques.

1208
01:09:03,572 --> 01:09:05,374
Mary, is the baby okay?

1209
01:09:05,407 --> 01:09:07,810
Yeah.

1210
01:09:07,843 --> 01:09:10,279
The book's gone.

1211
01:09:10,312 --> 01:09:11,747
But...

1212
01:09:11,780 --> 01:09:14,283
I guess the book worked.

1213
01:09:16,252 --> 01:09:17,520
It's a strange place
to end up.

1214
01:09:17,553 --> 01:09:18,521
It's underground.

1215
01:09:18,554 --> 01:09:19,755
Huh?

1216
01:09:19,788 --> 01:09:22,958
It's my parents'
weird apartment building.

1217
01:09:22,992 --> 01:09:26,262
I just--I don't see
their Volvo.

1218
01:09:49,518 --> 01:09:51,287
[chuckles]

1219
01:09:55,357 --> 01:09:57,459
That is the smell
of turkey.

1220
01:09:57,493 --> 01:10:00,496
Turkey
never smelled better.

1221
01:10:05,668 --> 01:10:06,969
Oh, it's a note
from my brother.

1222
01:10:07,002 --> 01:10:07,970
It says, um,

1223
01:10:08,003 --> 01:10:09,872
that they're
at midnight mass

1224
01:10:09,905 --> 01:10:12,675
and to forget about getting
the cranberry sauce.

1225
01:10:12,708 --> 01:10:14,877
They'll just go to the store
after church.

1226
01:10:14,910 --> 01:10:19,381
No cranberry,
I like this kind of problem.

1227
01:10:19,415 --> 01:10:21,717
So no key?

1228
01:10:21,750 --> 01:10:24,386
I have a plan.

1229
01:10:26,488 --> 01:10:29,458
[doorbell rings]

1230
01:10:31,460 --> 01:10:33,796
Feliz Navidad,
 Mrs. Martinez.

1231
01:10:33,829 --> 01:10:36,332
Oh, so good
to see you.

1232
01:10:36,365 --> 01:10:37,933
Uh, this is
my friend Jacques.

1233
01:10:37,967 --> 01:10:41,303
Do you still have
my parents' key by any chance?

1234
01:10:46,909 --> 01:10:50,446
(Mary)
 Gracias.

1235
01:10:50,479 --> 01:10:52,448
Et voilà.

1236
01:11:03,592 --> 01:11:04,560
This is it.

1237
01:11:04,593 --> 01:11:05,561
[laughs]

1238
01:11:05,594 --> 01:11:07,529
Cute.

1239
01:11:15,537 --> 01:11:17,606
You rest,

1240
01:11:17,640 --> 01:11:18,674
and I'll wash up, okay?

1241
01:11:18,707 --> 01:11:20,643
Okay.

1242
01:11:24,079 --> 01:11:26,448
I'll just watch
your tree grow.

1243
01:11:26,482 --> 01:11:28,484
That's
my favorite activity.

1244
01:12:23,005 --> 01:12:26,108
[whispering]
Jacques, I love you.

1245
01:14:24,760 --> 01:14:28,764
[glass shattering]

1246
01:14:32,668 --> 01:14:35,270
Mary?

1247
01:14:39,141 --> 01:14:40,075
[cocks gun]

1248
01:14:49,651 --> 01:14:50,619
Mary?

1249
01:14:50,652 --> 01:14:52,621
[door rattles]

1250
01:14:55,057 --> 01:14:56,191
Shit.

1251
01:14:56,225 --> 01:14:57,926
What the fuck
are you doing here?

1252
01:15:00,295 --> 01:15:01,296
Hi, I'm Jacques.

1253
01:15:01,330 --> 01:15:02,698
You're a jock?

1254
01:15:02,731 --> 01:15:05,133
No, I'm Jacques, French.

1255
01:15:05,167 --> 01:15:06,134
I'm French,

1256
01:15:06,168 --> 01:15:07,135
Mary's boyfriend--

1257
01:15:07,169 --> 01:15:12,241
I mean, husband,
but we are not married yet and--

1258
01:15:12,274 --> 01:15:13,976
these Volvo keys?

1259
01:15:14,009 --> 01:15:15,944
[tires squealing]

1260
01:15:20,148 --> 01:15:23,051
Cordobes!

1261
01:15:23,085 --> 01:15:26,655
Let her go!

1262
01:15:26,688 --> 01:15:28,590
This is between you and me.

1263
01:15:28,624 --> 01:15:29,358
Bastard.

1264
01:15:29,391 --> 01:15:30,359
[gunshot]

1265
01:15:30,392 --> 01:15:32,327
[Jacques groans]

1266
01:15:36,698 --> 01:15:39,902
[Mary whimpering]

1267
01:15:39,935 --> 01:15:42,871
Jacques.

1268
01:15:49,177 --> 01:15:52,014
[electronic whirring]

1269
01:15:52,047 --> 01:15:53,015
[gunshot]

1270
01:15:53,048 --> 01:15:54,983
[Mary screams]

1271
01:15:58,654 --> 01:16:00,756
Jacques?

1272
01:16:00,789 --> 01:16:03,825
[Mary crying]

1273
01:16:07,229 --> 01:16:08,764
(Jacques)
Mary, get away!

1274
01:16:08,797 --> 01:16:10,666
(Mary)
I can't!

1275
01:16:10,699 --> 01:16:12,634
Oh, my God.

1276
01:16:12,668 --> 01:16:14,202
Oh, my God.

1277
01:16:14,236 --> 01:16:16,738
Oh, my God.

1278
01:16:16,772 --> 01:16:18,674
(Laila)
Shoot her.

1279
01:16:18,707 --> 01:16:21,276
Now.

1280
01:16:21,310 --> 01:16:23,278
[growling]

1281
01:16:23,312 --> 01:16:28,750
[calliope music]

1282
01:16:28,784 --> 01:16:30,886
God damn you!

1283
01:16:30,919 --> 01:16:31,887
It's her...

1284
01:16:31,920 --> 01:16:33,322
No!

1285
01:16:33,355 --> 01:16:35,257
Or me.

1286
01:16:35,290 --> 01:16:37,292
[Cordobes grunting]

1287
01:16:37,326 --> 01:16:38,360
No!

1288
01:16:40,696 --> 01:16:42,664
[gunshot]

1289
01:16:42,698 --> 01:16:45,033
(Mary)
No!
Jacques.

1290
01:16:47,369 --> 01:16:49,271
Son of a bitch!

1291
01:17:09,024 --> 01:17:10,058
Kill the baby.

1292
01:17:10,092 --> 01:17:15,097
♪

1293
01:17:15,130 --> 01:17:17,132
[shouting]
Who are you?

1294
01:17:17,165 --> 01:17:18,967
Oh!

1295
01:17:19,001 --> 01:17:19,968
Careful.

1296
01:17:20,002 --> 01:17:22,671
No, Daddy, it's me.

1297
01:17:25,474 --> 01:17:27,209
Your little girl.

1298
01:17:39,454 --> 01:17:41,256
Shut the door!

1299
01:17:50,165 --> 01:17:52,100
(Laila)
Daddy.

1300
01:17:55,270 --> 01:18:00,409
You meant the world
to me, Daddy.

1301
01:18:14,523 --> 01:18:19,461
You meant the world
to me, Daddy.

1302
01:18:19,494 --> 01:18:20,462
[Mary groaning loudly]

1303
01:18:20,495 --> 01:18:23,031
Jacques, don't leave me!

1304
01:18:23,065 --> 01:18:25,200
Don't leave me!

1305
01:18:25,233 --> 01:18:28,203
Somebody help me.

1306
01:18:28,236 --> 01:18:29,871
[Mary sobbing]

1307
01:18:29,905 --> 01:18:32,107
Somebody, please--

1308
01:18:42,517 --> 01:18:43,485
[gunshot]

1309
01:19:00,102 --> 01:19:03,105
[gunshots]

1310
01:19:48,583 --> 01:19:50,318
Why'd you want this?

1311
01:19:52,621 --> 01:19:55,090
No wife.

1312
01:19:55,123 --> 01:19:58,260
No daughter.

1313
01:19:58,293 --> 01:20:01,229
No peace.

1314
01:20:01,263 --> 01:20:02,564
Go to Mary.

1315
01:20:02,597 --> 01:20:04,566
She needs you, Jacques.

1316
01:20:04,599 --> 01:20:07,502
Where were you?

1317
01:20:07,536 --> 01:20:08,503
Helping me?

1318
01:20:08,537 --> 01:20:09,938
You're alive.

1319
01:20:12,207 --> 01:20:13,642
What about him?

1320
01:20:13,675 --> 01:20:18,113
Like the Romans said,

1321
01:20:18,146 --> 01:20:20,448
"At the center of all things,
there are tears."

1322
01:20:23,251 --> 01:20:26,488
Demasiado corazón.

1323
01:20:26,521 --> 01:20:29,391
Too much heart.

1324
01:20:29,424 --> 01:20:32,360
Or hate.

1325
01:20:32,394 --> 01:20:33,361
Too much hate.

1326
01:20:33,395 --> 01:20:36,331
I keep reaching,

1327
01:20:36,364 --> 01:20:37,999
but I can't touch him.

1328
01:20:38,033 --> 01:20:39,000
I can't.

1329
01:20:39,034 --> 01:20:40,902
Allison.

1330
01:20:44,606 --> 01:20:46,541
Yes.

1331
01:20:54,449 --> 01:20:56,952
Don't leave me.

1332
01:21:02,657 --> 01:21:03,625
No, my love.

1333
01:21:03,658 --> 01:21:05,627
Your love?

1334
01:21:05,660 --> 01:21:08,430
My husband.

1335
01:21:08,463 --> 01:21:11,967
[sizzling noise]

1336
01:21:12,000 --> 01:21:14,102
Go.

1337
01:21:29,284 --> 01:21:31,386
We must go
and save Laila.

1338
01:21:38,460 --> 01:21:40,061
[baby cooing]

1339
01:21:40,095 --> 01:21:42,631
Come and say hello.

1340
01:21:47,636 --> 01:21:49,971
She won't bite.

1341
01:21:50,005 --> 01:21:51,172
It's a she?

1342
01:21:51,206 --> 01:21:53,408
Why not?

1343
01:21:53,441 --> 01:21:57,112
Uh, I just thought, uh--

1344
01:21:57,145 --> 01:21:58,380
okay.

1345
01:22:01,016 --> 01:22:02,984
Hello.

1346
01:22:03,018 --> 01:22:04,986
Hello.

1347
01:22:07,522 --> 01:22:09,491
What should I call her?

1348
01:22:09,524 --> 01:22:10,992
Her Majesty?

1349
01:22:11,026 --> 01:22:13,261
[snickering]

1350
01:22:13,295 --> 01:22:18,133
I call her "pumpkin."

1351
01:22:18,166 --> 01:22:19,134
Pumpkin?

1352
01:22:19,167 --> 01:22:20,135
Mm-hmm.

1353
01:22:20,168 --> 01:22:22,270
Oh, so, Pumpkins,

1354
01:22:22,304 --> 01:22:26,041
you are not
a dream, huh?

1355
01:22:27,809 --> 01:22:31,346
[baby crying]

1356
01:22:31,379 --> 01:22:34,182
Now the real trouble begins.

1357
01:22:34,215 --> 01:22:37,252
[both chuckle]

1358
01:22:37,285 --> 01:22:40,488
Pumpkins.

